<section class="lessons-learned">
    <div class="text-content">
        <h1>Lessons Learned</h1>
        <div class="lessons-flex-container">
            <div class="lesson-card left-wide">
                <h3>Design Iteration</h3>
                <p>Learned that digital simulations (Eagle/Fusion) rarely account for physical manufacturing tolerances. Iterating early saved weeks of debugging.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="lesson-card right-wide">
                <h3>Supply Chain</h3>
                <p>Navigating JLCPCB's manufacturing capabilities taught me to design for "DFM" (Design for Manufacturability) rather than just theoretical perfection.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-card full-width">
                <h3>Thermal Management</h3>
                <p>Discovered the importance of copper pours to dissipate heat from the Buck-Boost converter under high iPhone charging loads.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
